<h1>@HI{{dake}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> @N{{}} <strong>@HI{{dake}}</strong>
<li> <em>quantifier</em> <strong>@HI{{dake}}</strong> 
<li> @Vru{{}} <strong>@HI{{dake}}</strong>
<li> @Ai{{}} <strong>@HI{{dake}}</strong>
<li> @Ana{{}} <strong>@HI{{dake}}</strong>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{dake}}</strong> follows nouns and quantifiers and means "that's all" or "only".

<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{ano@KJ{{before^life}}niha@KJ{{one^degrees}}<strong>dake</strong>@KJ{{meeting}}imashita.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I met that professor only once.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{dake}}</strong> can also be used after a verb or an adjective.

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{morning}}ha@KT{{ko-hi-}}wo@KJ{{one^cupfuls^drink}}mu<strong>dake</strong>desu.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      In the morning I just drink a cup of coffee and that's all.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{kono@KJ{{hon}}ha@KJ{{tall}}i<strong>dake</strong>deomoshirokunai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      This book is just expensive and not interesting.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>
</p>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
When <strong>@HI{{dake}}</strong> follows a noun, the particle used with that
noun can precede or follow <strong>@HI{{dake}}</strong>, except for @HI{{ga}}
and @HI{{wo}}, which can optionally be used only after <strong>@HI{{dake}}</strong>.
</p>

<p>
@Vreru{{}} + <strong>@HI{{dake}}</strong> means "as much as one can".

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence">
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{jump}}reru<strong>dake</strong>@KJ{{jump}}rou.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Let's dance as much as we can (dance).
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>
</p>

